# Flag Image Licenses & Attributions

This file applies **only to flag images** used by the application
**FlagFinder** and included in this repository.

---

## Source of Images

All flag images are sourced from **Wikimedia Commons**
(https://commons.wikimedia.org).

The images are **not owned** by the repository or application author and
remain under their respective original licenses.

---

## Licensing Overview

Flag images in this project are licensed individually under one of the
following licenses:

- **Public Domain**
  (including PD-old, PD-ineligible, PD-government, PD-author)
- **CC0 1.0 Universal**
- **Creative Commons Attribution (CC BY)**
- **Creative Commons Attribution–ShareAlike (CC BY-SA)**

Images licensed under **Public Domain** or **CC0** may be used without
attribution.

Images licensed under **CC BY** or **CC BY-SA** require attribution, which
is provided in consolidated form below.

---

## Consolidated Image Credits

Attribution for all **CC BY** and **CC BY-SA** licensed images is provided
using the following format:

[Country / Entity] ([Years]) — [Author] — [License] — Wikimedia Commons

Afghanistan (1901 - 1919) - QWerk - CC BY-SA 3.0 - Wikimedia Commons
Afghanistan (1928) - Fornax - CC BY-SA 3.0 - Wikimedia Commons
Afghanistan (2001 - 2002) - Saul ip (derivative work of MS05L) - CC BY-SA 3.0 - Wikimedia Commons
Andorra (1939 - 1949) - Heralder - CC BY-SA 4.0 - Wikipedia Commons
Andorra (1949 - 1959) - Heralder - CC BY-SA 4.0 - Wikipedia Commons

Changes made to images may include resizing, format conversion, or minor
visual adjustments. No significant artistic modifications have been made.

---

## License Texts

The full texts of the applicable licenses are available at:

- CC BY 4.0  
